[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA Jazzer-based fuzzing run triggered a critical security issue related to remote [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNDI lookups within Apache Log4j. The fuzzer input led to a [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception, indicating that attacker-controlled JNDI [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mURLs could be used to perform remote code execution or data exfiltration. The stack[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrace shows the issue originates in `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` and propagates[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough Log4j’s `JndiLookup`, `StrSubstitutor`, and `PatternLayout` components [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring normal logging operations.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A Jazzer sanitizer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected and halted a JNDI [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup using a remote URL. Such lookups are inherently dangerous because, depending[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the Java version, they can fetch and execute remote code or leak sensitive [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minformation from the application environment.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is classified as “Remote JNDI Lookup,” a critical security [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability that can lead to remote code execution or unauthorized data access [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen an attacker controls the lookup URL.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The exception `com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemote JNDI Lookup` is thrown at  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    `[0m[1;35mNamingContextLookup.lookupHook[0m[1;39m([0m[39mNamingContextLookup.kt:[0m[1;36m61[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The lookup originates in Log4j’s [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup` method  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Subsequent calls flow through Log4j’s variable interpolation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Interpolator`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`StrSubstitutor`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and message formatting [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MessagePatternConverter`, [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PatternLayout`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The logging pipeline continues through `AbstractOutputStreamAppender.append` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `AppenderControl.callAppender` until the fuzzer harness’s [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput` method invokes Log4j[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Affected code areas for investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Jazzer sanitizer:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto understand how remote URLs are detected[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand flagged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Log4j core lookup mechanism:  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.Interpolator`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.StrSubstitutor`  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Log4j formatting and appending:  [0m                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Fuzzer harness entry point:  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `com.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto trace how inputs [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraverse the logging code[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Modify core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the static default for ENABLE_JNDI from “true” to read a system [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. “log4j2.enableJndiLookup”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a secure default of false:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI = [0m[1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Expose this flag via a public static method:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – public static boolean [0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return ENABLE_JNDI; [0m[1;39m}[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. In the [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method, enforce both the enable‐flag and restrict lookups [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto local JNDI namespaces only:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – If key is null → return null.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Compute jndiName = [0m[1;35mconvertJndiName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – If not ENABLE_JNDI → return null immediately.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – If jndiName does not start with the safe container prefix [0m[1;39m([0m[39m“java:”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e. it appears to be a remote URL such as ldap:, rmi:, http:[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlog a warning and return null.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Otherwise proceed with [0m[1;35mctx.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mjndiName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Retain exactly the same exception‐throwing behavior only for disallowed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote lookups if desired, or simply return null to silently drop them.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Modify [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/Interpolator.java:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In the no-arg constructor, guard the registration of the “jndi” lookup by [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking the new flag:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Remove the unconditional [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Instead:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – This ensures that, by default, no “jndi:” variable expansions are even [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregistered.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve existing functionality:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – By using a system property, existing applications that rely on JNDI lookups [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvia Log4j can re-enable the feature by setting ‟-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m” at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstartup.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Local JNDI resource lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain supported when the flag [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis true.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Documentation:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Update the Log4j user manual or release notes to document the new system [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlog4j2.enableJndiLookup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, its default [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and its effect.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Mention that remote protocols [0m[1;39m([0m[39mldap:, rmi:, http:[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are disallowed even when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe flag is off; when the flag is on, only trusted local namespaces are permitted [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby default.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Testing:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No changes are needed to the fuzzer harness or existing unit tests.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Add new unit tests in the Log4j core test suite to verify that:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • With the flag off, “$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:ldap:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mevil[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m” → null [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand logs a warning[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • With the flag on, “$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/jdbc/MyDB[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m” → performs lookup [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mmock or context stub[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • With the flag on, “$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:rmi:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95mevil[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m” → still blocked.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Disables dangerous remote JNDI lookups by default, eliminating the vulnerability.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Leverages a well-known, low-impact system property for opt-in behavior—this [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmirrors patterns in other security fixes [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. disabling lookups unless explicitly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-enabled[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Keeps local JNDI support available for applications that depend on it, preserving[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbackward‐compatibility when explicitly enabled.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Avoids changes to harness code, tests, or external dependencies, focusing the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch solely on Log4j core lookup logic.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Narrowly scopes checks to JndiLookup and Interpolator, ensuring minimal side [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meffects elsewhere in the logging pipeline.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.LoggerConfig.log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLoggerConfig.jav[0m[1;92ma:407[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.LoggerConfig.log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLoggerConfig.jav[0m[1;92ma:368[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.Logger.log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogger.jav[0m[1;92ma:110[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.spi.AbstractLogger.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mAbstractLogger.jav[0m[1;92ma:1916[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:42[0m[1;39m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn OSS-Fuzz run against a Log4j2 fuzz target triggered a [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception due to an unguarded remote JNDI lookup in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`. A candidate patch was proposed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto disable JNDI lookups by default, gate them behind a system property, and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestrict lookups to safe JNDI namespaces. After applying the patch, the Maven build[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof `log4j-core` failed with two compilation errors in `JndiLookup.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`illegal [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of type` and `[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, preventing successful fuzz-target integration.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer-based fuzzer invoked the Log4j2 lookup mechanism with a crafted [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput that led to a remote JNDI lookup via `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39m…[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Jazzer sanitizer hook detected this as a security issue [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI Lookup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, citing the risk of remote code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution or data exfiltration.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack trace shows the call path through `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`JndiLookup.lookup`, and the log4j core formatting pipeline [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. `StrSubstitutor`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`PatternLayout`, `AbstractOutputStreamAppender`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarning via `AbstractLogger.warn` before the crash.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The proposed changes to `JndiLookup.java` and `Interpolator.java` include:  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `JndiLookup.java`:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Change `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` to  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI = [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Add a public static method  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```java[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       public static boolean [0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Update both `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to return `null`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif JNDI is disabled.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Introduce namespace checks so that only names starting with `[0m[32m"java:"[0m[39m` or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"java:comp/env/"[0m[39m` are looked up; otherwise log a warning and return `null`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Log errors on `NamingException`.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `Interpolator.java`:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Only register the `[0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m` lookup if `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`true`.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Application and Build Log  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch was applied via a standard diff to the files under [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A full Maven rebuild [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mvn clean install -am -pl :log4j-api,:log4j-core`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompleted successfully for `log4j-api` but failed for `log4j-core`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The relevant errors are:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/src/logging-log4j2/core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/[0m[95mJn[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mdiLookup.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m][0m[39m illegal start of type  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/src/logging-log4j2/core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/[0m[95mJn[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95mdiLookup.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m40[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These errors indicate a Java syntax issue at the location where [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was inserted [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m of `JndiLookup.java`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, suggesting [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched braces or misplaced declarations.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `JndiLookup.java` structure: verify class-level braces and the placement of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe new `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method and comments/Javadoc.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Imports and closing of previous declarations in `JndiLookup.java` to ensure no[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdangling comment or semicolon is causing the syntax error.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `Interpolator` constructor in `Interpolator.java` to confirm correct [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditional registration of `[0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any shared utility methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `convertJndiName`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to see if their [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignatures or usages were affected by the patch.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build configurations or coding conventions that may impose restrictions on [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatic field initialization or method ordering.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root-cause analysis or fixes are included here. This report documents the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity finding, the attempted remediation, and the resulting build failures for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfurther review.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The compilation errors [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`illegal start of type`, `[0m[32m';'[0m[39m expected`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at line [0m[1;36m40[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicate misplaced or malformed declarations immediately after the class opening. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is due to the patch inserting the `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method and modifying [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` without aligning braces or comments correctly.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Actions:**  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. Replace the mutable `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` with an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmutable `private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI = [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly once, as the first class-level field below the class declaration. Ensure [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe initializer is a single-statement [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot split across lines without proper [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemicolon[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Example:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI =[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. Immediately after this field [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand after any Javadoc on it, if present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsert the new public method:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static boolean [0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c. Remove the obsolete setter `public static void [0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mold `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` getter to avoid conflicting symbols.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     d. Verify that the Javadoc comment `[0m[35m/[0m[39m** JNDI resource path prefix… *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` and the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration of `CONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX` remain intact, with no [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraneous braces, stray annotations, or syntax errors.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Refactor Lookup Logic in JndiLookup**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Preserve existing behavior of `[0m[1;35mconvertJndiName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In both `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Early-return `null` if `ENABLE_JNDI` is `false`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Normalize the name via `[0m[1;35mconvertJndiName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` once.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Enforce namespace restrictions [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`java:` or `jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Catch `NamingException` and log at `error` level.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure imports for `org.apache.logging.log4j.status.StatusLogger` or [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequivalent `LOGGER` exist [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe class already has a static `LOGGER` instance[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Guard Registration in Interpolator**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `Interpolator`'s zero-arg constructor, replace the unconditional[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any trailing semicolons or misplaced braces. Confirm that the braces of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `if` block align with the constructor’s scope.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Validate Class and Method Order**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `JndiLookup.java`, maintain this order:  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Class JavaDoc & `@Plugin` annotation  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Class declaration & opening brace  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Static fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ENABLE_JNDI`, `CONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Public static methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`isJndiEnabled`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m5[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Constructor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif any[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or interface method implementations [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`lookup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Private helper [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`convertJndiName`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m7[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Closing brace  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run `mvn compile` to ensure syntax correctness.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Justification and Side-effects**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserves existing logic**: The `convertJndiName` helper and lookup methods [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain unchanged except for the gating and namespace check.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Security improvement**: Disables remote JNDI lookups by default, mitigating [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRCE risks.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Backward compatibility**: Users can opt in via the `log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem property. Existing tests/harness code remain unaffected; JNDI lookups simply[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn `null` when disabled.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Potential side-effects**: Third-party code relying on JNDI lookups must set [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe system property explicitly. Document this change in release notes.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Final Verification**  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run `mvn clean install -pl :log4j-core` to confirm the build passes.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute existing unit tests for `JndiLookup` and `Interpolator` to ensure no [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregressions.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm the fuzz target still registers or omits `jndi` per the property [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout harness modifications.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update documentation or release notes to instruct users on the new property [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn automated security test flagged a critical issue in Log4j’s JNDI lookup [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmechanism: unvalidated remote JNDI URLs may lead to remote code execution or data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexfiltration. A patch attempt was made to disable JNDI lookups by default [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcontrolled via a new system property[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, restrict lookups to safe namespaces, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremove the old mutable flags. After applying the patch, the build fails in core [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests because several test classes still reference the removed method [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, resulting in “cannot find symbol” compilation errors.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A Jazzer-based fuzzer reported `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI Lookup`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace shows Log4j’s `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is invoked when logging a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwarning in a simple fuzzing harness.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Unrestricted JNDI lookups can fetch remote data or execute remote code, depending[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon JDK behavior.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `JndiLookup.java`:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Replaced the mutable static `ENABLE_JNDI` flag with a `private static final` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield initialized from the system property `log4j2.enableJndiLookup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Introduced `public static boolean [0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` accessor.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Removed the old setter `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and getter `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Added logic in `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to normalize the name once and restrict it to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`java:` or `jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `Interpolator.java`:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Changed the lookup registration: only add the `[0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m` lookup if [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns true.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResulting Build Errors  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Tests in `core/src/test/java/[0m[33m...[0m[39m` reference the removed method [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation errors appear in:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest.java`  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `JndiLookupTest.java`  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - `InterpolatorTest.java`  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Errors report “cannot find symbol: method [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m” at several lines.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All core test classes that directly call or mock `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` need[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdates.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest` suite, since it hardcodes the JNDI-enablement [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtoggle.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `JndiLookupTest` and `InterpolatorTest` for assumptions around lookup [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregistration and behavior.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any other code [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., integration tests or examples[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that use the old [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msetter/getter APIs or expect JNDI lookups to be unconditionally available.[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:    public void [0m[1;35mtestLookupWithDefaultInterpolator[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m! [0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview of the root cause  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   All failing tests call the removed method `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand used [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto rely on the mutable `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the new design has:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A `private static final boolean ENABLE_JNDI` driven by the system property [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A single public accessor `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Therefore, the tests must be updated to:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Use `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Drive JNDI‐enabled behavior by setting/clearing the system property in test [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msetup/teardown, rather than toggling a setter.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-level patch steps  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest.java  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      i.  In `@BeforeClass [0m[1;35msetupClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, before obtaining the LoggerContext, add  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"true"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ii. Replace the runtime guard  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         with  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      iii. In `@AfterClass [0m[1;35mcleanupClass[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, after clearing the XMLConfiguration [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty, add  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.clearProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. JndiLookupTest.java  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      i.  In `@Before`, after `[0m[1;35mMockContextFactory.setAsInitial[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"true"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ii. Replace  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m! [0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         with  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m! [0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      iii. In `@After`, after `[0m[1;35mMockContextFactory.revertSetAsInitial[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.clearProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. InterpolatorTest.java  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      i.  In `@BeforeClass [0m[1;35mbefore[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, before `[0m[1;35mMockContextFactory.setAsInitial[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"true"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ii. Replace both guards  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m! [0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         with  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m! [0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m return; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      iii. In `@AfterClass [0m[1;35mafter[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, after clearing the ThreadContext/system key, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         `[0m[1;35mSystem.clearProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of existing functionality  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Core logic in `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `Interpolator` remains untouched.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests will now correctly enable JNDI via the intended mechanism [0m[1;39m([0m[39msystem [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, instantiate lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding “jndi”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and exercise code paths that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere previously guarded by the removed setter/getter.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clearing the property in teardown ensures no cross-test pollution.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Aligns tests with the new immutable, system-property–driven toggle in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`JndiLookup`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Avoids reintroducing deprecated setters/getters in production code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwould bloat the API[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Meets the requirement not to alter harness/fuzzer logic or external [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures tests pass under the new security-first default [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`JNDI disabled unless[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly enabled`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side effects and mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introducing the system property in tests may potentially affect other code [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat reads `log4j2.enableJndiLookup`. However, each test suite sets+clears the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty in its own lifecycle methods, so the impact is scoped and cleaned up.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new dependencies or broad catch blocks are added.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar pattern exists in other tests that control features via system [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperties [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `XMLConfigurationFactory.CONFIGURATION_FILE_PROPERTY`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already centralizes the toggle; tests [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply invoke it.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
