[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer reported a critical Java exception                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup`[1m)[0m originating from Log4j’s `JndiLookup` mechanism. To exercise and validate  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JNDI-related tests, a patch was introduced in three core test classes to:           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Set the system property `log4j2.[33menableJndiLookup[0m=[35mtrue[0m` in setup methods and clear [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         it in teardowns.                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Replace calls to `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` with `[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         After applying the patch, the build failed with compilation errors: the method      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` could not be found in                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzing harness triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         due to remote JNDI lookups in Log4j.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace highlights the path:                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              NamingContextLookup.lookupHook → JndiLookup.lookup →                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Interpolator.resolveVariable → PatternLayout → AbstractOutputStreamAppender →       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Logger.warn → fuzzer entry point [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`[1m)[0m.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The finding underscores that if attacker-controlled URLs reach Log4j’s JNDI    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lookup plugin, they can lead to remote code execution or data exfiltration.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerability surface lies in                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup` and its integration with Log4j’s  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         pattern substitution and appenders.                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Tests for routing appenders, lookup plugins, and interpolator behaviors        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         currently guard JNDI tests behind a flag check [1m([0m`[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Modified three test classes under                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `core/src/test/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/[33m...[0m`:                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              a. RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The compilation errors in the test classes stem from referencing a non-existent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Additionally, setting the system property [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m` in tests currently has no effect, because `JndiLookup` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads only its internal static flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ENABLE_JNDI`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and never consults system [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperties.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Goals  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Introduce a public alias method `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `JndiLookup` so tests [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompile.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Enhance the existing `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to read the system property [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas tests set and clear it[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a fallback to the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatic `ENABLE_JNDI` field.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Preserve the ability to programmatically toggle JNDI lookups via [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and maintain the original behavior when no system property[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis set.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java`:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Add an import for `PropertiesUtil`:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      import org.apache.logging.log4j.util.PropertiesUtil;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Define a constant for the system property key [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabove or below the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` field[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private static final String SYS_PROP_ENABLE_JNDI = [0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Modify `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to read the system property with fallback:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Read system property first; fallback to static flag[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                               [0m[1;35m.getBooleanProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSYS_PROP_ENABLE_JNDI, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Add the missing alias method so tests referring to `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompile:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * Alias for [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, matching test expectations.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      public static boolean [0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Leave the existing `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` intact, so code that toggles JNDI[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprogrammatically continues to function.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introducing `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves the compilation errors without altering[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtest code.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reading the system property `[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m[39m` aligns with the tests’[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muse of `System.setProperty`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`clearProperty`, enabling JNDI lookup dynamically in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retaining fallback to the `ENABLE_JNDI` static variable preserves backward [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompatibility for code relying on `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications are made to harness or test code beyond what is absolutely [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary; existing tests and fuzzing logic remain intact.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Each call to `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` now invokes [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getBooleanProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which reads [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand caches[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem property or fallback. This adds minimal overhead comparable to other lookups[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min Log4j.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Users setting `log4j2.enableJndiLookup` at startup will now consistently [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol JNDI enablement; ensure documentation is updated if desired.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other lookups or behaviors in `Interpolator`, `PatternLayout`, or appenders[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare affected, since JNDI logic remains gated by `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Reference  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar pattern exists in other Log4j lookup implementations [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `env` or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`sys` lookups[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that read system properties via `PropertiesUtil`. Use those as a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguideline for consistency.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:42[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing harness triggered a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` due to a “Remote [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JNDI Lookup” in Log4j’s `JndiLookup` class. The patch attempt introduced a new      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         system‐property flag [1m([0m`log4j2.enableJndiLookup`[1m)[0m and modified                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` [1m([0mand added an alias `[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m to consult that  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         flag instead of the hard‐coded `ENABLE_JNDI` field. After applying the patch, the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         fuzzer still crashes in `[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` [1m([0mnow at line [1;36m61[0m[1m)[0m, indicating that     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JNDI lookups remain enabled by default and the property‐check logic did not prevent [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the vulnerability from being exercised.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer security sanitizer detected a critical JNDI lookup during log message [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         formatting.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace highlights:                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` → `JndiLookup.lookup` →                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `Interpolator.lookup` → `StrSubstitutor.*` → `PatternLayout` → logger append →      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The root symptom is that, by default, `[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` performs a JNDI [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lookup on attacker-controlled input, which can lead to remote code execution.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The static field `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` in               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.java` effectively leaves lookups enabled unconditionally.               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Existing code paths in `[1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` rely on `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` returning        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `true`.                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No existing configuration mechanism was gating JNDI resolution at runtime in   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the patched code.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Added a new constant in `JndiLookup.java`:                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              private static final String SYS_PROP_ENABLE_JNDI = [32m"log4j2.enableJndiLookup"[0m;  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Updated `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` to consult                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m[1;35m.getBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, defaulting to the         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         original `ENABLE_JNDI` flag:                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              public static boolean [1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  return [1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                      [1;35m.getBooleanProperty[0m[1m([0mSYS_PROP_ENABLE_JNDI, ENABLE_JNDI[1m)[0m;                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Introduced an alias `[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` for consistency with tests:              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              public static boolean [1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m [1m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                  return [1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              ```                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Patch Result                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The patched code still triggers `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` at               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0mJndiLookup.jav[1;92ma:61[0m[1m)[0m`, one line below the original [1;36m60[0m.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace is otherwise identical, confirming that:                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • The new property‐check logic did not disable JNDI lookups by default.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • The fuzzer did not set `log4j2.[33menableJndiLookup[0m=[35mfalse[0m`, so `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         returned `true`.                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No changes in the harness or logging configuration were made, so the           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         vulnerability remains reachable.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The `[1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` implementation in `JndiLookup.java`: confirm that the new    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` guard is actually invoked at the start of the method before any    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         network call.                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Interaction between `[1;35mPropertiesUtil.getProperties[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` and system properties:    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         verify that `log4j2.enableJndiLookup` can be set at JVM startup or via code in the  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         expected manner.                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Call sites in other lookup or interpolator classes [1m([0m`Interpolator`,            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StrSubstitutor`[1m)[0m to see if alternate JNDI paths exist.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Initialization and defaulting logic for `ENABLE_JNDI`—consider whether the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         static field should default to `false`.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The overall Log4j configuration loading mechanism: check if there are multiple [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         entry points or overrides for lookups that bypass `[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String var[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:     * Resolves the specified variable. This implementation will try to extract[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:     * a variable prefix from the given variable name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe first colon [0m[1;39m([0m[32m':'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:     * used as prefix separator[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. It then passes the name of the variable with[0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:     * resolved[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal LogEvent event, String var[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapi/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/util/PropertiesUtil.jav[0m[1;92ma:118[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m126[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:    public boolean [0m[1;35mgetBooleanProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefaultValue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:        final String prop = [0m[1;35mgetStringProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprop == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? defaultValue : [0m[32m"true"[0m[1;35m.equalsIgnoreCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mprop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Summary of Root Cause[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method’s guard uses the hard-coded [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` flag directly, bypassing the new `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` system-property [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `ENABLE_JNDI` remains `true` by default, and [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m never calls [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, remote JNDI lookups stay enabled unless callers explicitly call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Required Changes in JndiLookup.java[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the default of `ENABLE_JNDI` from `true` to `false`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – This ensures that, out of the box, JNDI lookups are disabled for security. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – Users who require JNDI lookups can re-enable them via:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • System property `-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         • Runtime call `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Modify the lookup guard to call `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of reading [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` directly  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – At the start of `public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent event, String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, replace[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey == null || !ENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey == null || ![0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – This invokes the system-property logic, honoring `log4j2.enableJndiLookup`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Retain the `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` setter and the alias `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserve existing API and test expectations.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Patch Outline[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java`:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Line [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m: Change[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = false;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Lines [0m[1;36m54[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m56[0m[39m: Change[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey == null || !ENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return null;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey == null || ![0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return null;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Leave the `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` implementations [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem-property logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unchanged.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Rationale & Side-Effect Management[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By defaulting `ENABLE_JNDI` to `false`, Log4j’s JNDI lookup is disabled out of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe box, mitigating the critical vulnerability without requiring users to opt in.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The system-property `log4j2.enableJndiLookup` retains full flexibility for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musers who legitimately rely on JNDI lookups.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changing the guard to `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` ensures the property mechanism is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mactually used.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing unit tests that reference `[0m[1;35misJndiEnabled[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to pass.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to harness or test code are necessary. The fuzzer harness [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now observe lookups returning null, eliminating the [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Verification Steps[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Write or update a small integration test that:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Invokes `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.lookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mevent, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without setting any system property;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpect `null`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Invokes with `-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndiLookup[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`; expect an attempted JNDI [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor a `NamingException` in test[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Invokes `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at runtime; expect lookup to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproceed.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run existing test suite to ensure no regressions.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rerun the Jazzer harness: confirm no `Remote JNDI Lookup` finding by default.[0m  [2m                [0m
